pd      16      0.02    0.01    8       0.0%    0.0%    0.489   0.9991  0.8469  0.9938  0.6171  0.8453
</pre>
  <p class="nice-wrap">
    The script will analyze both mark files, it will try to match each
    marked segment, construct the global confusion matrix and print out the
    calculated stats. Optionally, it can write the results to a file and/or
    generate a consufion matrix graph (see script help menu for more info using
    the argument <code>-h</code>).
  </p>
  <p class="nice-wrap">
    If you have several files to process, use instead a wildcard pattern (e.g.
    <code>Ap*.csv</code>) that will match all the <code>.csv</code>
    files starting with <code>Ap</code>, and the script will take
    care of the rest. However, the filenames must contain <code>-manual</code>
    and <code>-auto</code> suffixes.
  </p>

